<node id="DEBT TO ASSETS RATIO">
  <data key="d0">METRIC</data>
  <data key="d1">The Debt to Assets Ratio is a critical financial metric that indicates the proportion of a company's total liabilities relative to its total assets. This ratio provides insights into how much of a company's assets are financed by debt, offering an understanding of the company's financial leverage and stability.

In various instances, this ratio has been reported at 25%, indicating a balanced approach between asset acquisition and debt management. A ratio of 0.4 signifies that the company's debt is 40% of its total assets, demonstrating a balanced financial leverage. In other scenarios, it was noted to be as high as 50%, reflecting a moderate level of debt in relation to the company's assets.

For instance, the Debt to Assets Ratio for EcoGuard Solutions stood at 0.4, showing that 40% of its assets are funded through debt. Similarly, JetWing Aviation and Energex also reported a ratio of 0.4, indicating balanced financial leverage. However, Retail Emporium had a significantly higher ratio of 70%, signifying a substantial level of debt relative to its total assets.

The Debt to Assets Ratio is crucial for stakeholders as it provides an insight into the company's financial stability and solvency. A lower ratio indicates that a significant portion of the company's assets are financed by equity, which is generally considered safer than debt financing. Conversely, a higher ratio suggests more reliance on debt, which could potentially increase financial risk.

In summary, the Debt to Assets Ratio provides valuable information about how much of a company's assets are funded by debt, thus offering insights into its financial leverage and stability. It's essential for investors, creditors, and other stakeholders to understand this ratio when evaluating a company's overall financial health.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-337f69c70d0d25eb1377f55716d42ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8997bc18dca7cba5d79e1809401489b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d5b9a6230849cbd0ceb12bdacc8d930&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a238ff5c2448b41d18fa44957345522&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4c8f45cb1304b97e112f330c9db56a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2c6668c781612bc4cfed9959b3a72af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0396f321b40762e78e7ee6efabe134d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-18caea3ff0aef95985c460898a0bec16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c480ee0c723afca3f22c9c6fe232f30d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83e808b8711f18dda66b0fc1c4ad9351&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aed2d109c9525bda21552db168fc971d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-295d0141abde05a4719f3b383d07c788&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a755f31a89c0b0f4817758389cb1c71a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1985fe44245a74e561ef855d9b45c59c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f76e6f51915ca0ca4e1fa04d61ed412d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2add3db4f644e304d4288964b61b2a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68ab7d5ce1623cc04843c92af4bded19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0520afccc9bc337124b72af928229db6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8199cc796723aac9047ec54e229d202a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7464e6549bfd33747c77ecb5cb886c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a43321794b440f22a3185e50b3242b68&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc998caae59f4c4aed5f7b3ee1a7ef66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac24a72c7e4b25443159dc621feeb211&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b66c40857191417b60e60f565f026a50&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11493ee1e077bc69eb110a807eb081c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-574b9a5209d426ecc05b332c4f3cb54e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-affa74002724dde27455d0cbc1953370&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ca9523bd7f6636f9a9ba3b9957651f8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f6652c83cca0e94f4bd8f4bcadaeb60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3feddd6ebe8f5225d8068101fb9790fb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 49}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 276}]</data>
