<node id="$300 MILLION">
  <data key="d0">METRIC</data>
  <data key="d1">In 2019, Vanguard Media Group's net profit amounted to $300 million, reflecting its ability to grow its operating income, efficiently control costs, and minimize non-recurring losses.&lt;SEP&gt;Shareholder equity reached $300 million.&lt;SEP&gt;Shareholder equity totaling $300 million represents the equity belonging to shareholders at the end of the accounting period.&lt;SEP&gt;The amount of investment made by Evergreen Consumer Goods Co. in Project EverFresh.&lt;SEP&gt;The company generated a cash flow of $300 million, influenced by operating activities, investment activities, and financing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;The global box office revenue was projected to be $300 million for The Great Escape.&lt;SEP&gt;The shareholder equity of Retail Emporium was $300 million, influenced by net profit, dividend distribution, and capital reserves.&lt;SEP&gt;The total amount of debts the company is obligated to repay at the end of the accounting period.&lt;SEP&gt;The total amount of equity belonging to shareholders for HealthLife Solutions at the end of the specified accounting period.&lt;SEP&gt;The total amount of shareholder equity belonging to EduCorp at the end of the accounting period.&lt;SEP&gt;The total assets reached by InnovaTech at a certain point were $300 million.</data>
