<node id="FINANCIAL LEVERAGE">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">Financial leverage refers to the use of debt to finance assets, which can amplify returns but also increases risk if those debts are not managed effectively.&lt;SEP&gt;Refers to the extent of a company's reliance on debt financing relative to its assets.&lt;SEP&gt;Stated at 32.0%, reflecting the company's reliance on leverage in its operations.&lt;SEP&gt;The financial leverage of a company, as indicated by its debt to assets ratio, shows how much of its assets are funded through debt.</data>
