<node id="MEDIA CORP">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">MediaCorp is a leading media organization focused on managing risks through internal control systems, sustainable development, social responsibility, and diversified investments.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a leading organization in the media industry involved in financing activities, expansion plans, and asset restructuring.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a major corporation that has invested in various startups including Project Vision and acquired Digital Media Solutions.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a major media conglomerate known for its extensive reach and influence across various sectors including television, entertainment, and digital platforms.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a major player in the media industry known for its comprehensive financial reporting.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a major player in the media industry, focusing on strategic planning and investment in various sectors.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a media and entertainment company demonstrating solid financial performance.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a media company that distributed dividends to shareholders based on its financial performance.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a media company that focuses on governance structure, ethics, transparency, stakeholder engagement, and sustainable development initiatives.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a media organization that established a Whistleblower Protection Program to promote transparency and accountability.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a media organization that has expanded its operations through acquisitions.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a media organization that underwent debt restructuring and dividend distribution.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a prominent media organization that has been expanding its business and enhancing market competitiveness.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a publicly listed media company on the NYSE, headquartered in New York, United States. It specializes in media production and distribution.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a telecommunications and media services company that aims to allocate resources for research and development initiatives while mitigating potential financial risks through diversification strategies, talent acquisition, and enhanced marketing efforts.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is a telecommunications company that prioritized information disclosure and internal control measures.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is an international multimedia company that aims to improve its governance practices.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is an organization that experienced senior management changes including a new CEO appointment.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is an organization that faced governance challenges and implemented measures to address them.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is an organization that focuses on compliance with regulations affecting corporate governance practices.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is an organization that has conducted strategic market analyses and acquisitions.&lt;SEP&gt;MediaCorp is an organization that implemented changes in its Code of Conduct.</data>
