<node id="DEFENDANT">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">A defendant is a person accused of committing a crime, typically being at the center of various legal proceedings and facing charges related to different offenses such as fraud, theft, assault, tax evasion, or embezzlement. This individual has been afforded constitutional rights to appeal judgments and may be involved in specific incidents like disposing of blood-stained clothing or weapon remnants, engaging in threatening behavior towards others, causing accidents through reckless driving, or participating in financial misconduct with their company. The defendant is also informed about the right to legal representation throughout these proceedings and may have connections to various locations such as businesses, grocery stores, residential areas, or retail establishments.</data>
