  <data key="d1">A person involved in public disturbances in Quailwood during January 15, 2023 to February 5, 2023.&lt;SEP&gt;An individual detained by the Quailwood Police Department under suspicion of picking quarrels and provoking trouble after a series of disturbances.&lt;SEP&gt;An individual involved in obstructing traffic near a school zone based on CCTV footage and eyewitness accounts.&lt;SEP&gt;An individual who forcibly took merchandise from market kiosks without paying, causing significant financial losses to vendors.&lt;SEP&gt;An individual who is charged with picking quarrels and provoking trouble near a school zone.&lt;SEP&gt;An individual who was considered for sentencing based on her disruptive actions.&lt;SEP&gt;Defendant in a criminal case within the jurisdiction of the 9th Judicial Circuit.&lt;SEP&gt;The individual found guilty of picking quarrels and provoking trouble under Article No. 293 of the Criminal Code.&lt;SEP&gt;Y. Nelson is a female Caucasian individual born on December 5, 1981, and currently resides at 79 Yorkshire Street in Quailwood. Her occupation is listed as Barista.&lt;SEP&gt;Y. Nelson is a person who has been involved in financial losses and theft incidents as per vendor statements.&lt;SEP&gt;Y. Nelson is a person who was involved in disputes, verbally harassing bystanders, and creating a hostile environment in public spaces.&lt;SEP&gt;Y. Nelson is a person who was observed to frequently insult customers and instigate public disputes, causing negative impacts on local businesses.&lt;SEP&gt;Y. Nelson is described in the text as having made obstructions and uttered obscene outbursts, leading to chaos and fear among parents and school staff during school dismissal.&lt;SEP&gt;Y. Nelson was issued an arrest warrant by the Glenwood, Quailwood Procuratorate due to disruptive and aggressive behaviors.</data>
