<node id="FATIGUE">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">A feeling of extreme tiredness or exhaustion.&lt;SEP&gt;A persistent feeling of tiredness and lack of energy despite adequate rest or sleep patterns.&lt;SEP&gt;A persistent feeling of tiredness or lack of energy.&lt;SEP&gt;A state of exhaustion or lack of energy, commonly reported by patients as a symptom associated with other health conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;A state of feeling tired, weak, or lacking energy due to the condition.&lt;SEP&gt;A state of physical or mental exhaustion characterized by lack of energy and strength.&lt;SEP&gt;Fatigue is a feeling of exhaustion or lack of energy that can accompany hyperthyroidism.&lt;SEP&gt;Fatigue is another accompanying symptom of the condition mentioned in the text.&lt;SEP&gt;Fatigue is characterized by extreme tiredness or lack of energy that does not improve with rest. It can be caused by various factors including medical conditions, lifestyle choices, or mental state changes.&lt;SEP&gt;Fatigue is often reported as a feeling of exhaustion or lack of energy.&lt;SEP&gt;Persistent feeling of tiredness reported by the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;Persistent tiredness or lack of energy experienced by the individual.&lt;SEP&gt;Persistent tiredness that affects daily activities and overall well-being.</data>
