<node id="GENERAL CONDITION">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">A comprehensive assessment of the patient's overall health status, including vital signs and systemic examination findings.&lt;SEP&gt;A general condition refers to the overall state or health status of a person, which can include physical, mental, and emotional aspects. It is often assessed as part of a comprehensive medical examination.&lt;SEP&gt;An assessment of the patient's overall health status.&lt;SEP&gt;An evaluation of the patient's overall physical and mental state.&lt;SEP&gt;An overview of the patient's current state, encompassing various vital signs and physical observations.&lt;SEP&gt;Assessment of overall health status, including vital signs and initial observations.&lt;SEP&gt;Details general physical condition such as temperature, pulse, respiration, and blood pressure.&lt;SEP&gt;General condition of the individual as assessed during a physical examination.&lt;SEP&gt;General physical condition includes temperature, pulse, respiration, and blood pressure.&lt;SEP&gt;Physical examination details including temperature of 98.6°F, pulse rate of 76 bpm, respiration rate of 16 breaths per minute, and blood pressure of 120/80 mmHg indicate a healthy state for the individual being examined.&lt;SEP&gt;Symptoms observed during a physical examination including high temperature, rapid pulse, slow respiration, and normal blood pressure.&lt;SEP&gt;The general condition includes temperature (37.0°C), pulse rate (80 bpm), respiration rate (18 breaths/min) and blood pressure reading (135/80 mmHg). This provides an overview of the individual's physiological state.&lt;SEP&gt;The general condition of the patient as assessed during the physical examination.&lt;SEP&gt;The general condition refers to the overall health status of an individual.&lt;SEP&gt;The general condition section provides an overview of the patient's vital signs including temperature, pulse, respiration, and blood pressure.&lt;SEP&gt;The general health status and well-being of the patient assessed during the physical examination.&lt;SEP&gt;The individual's overall physical state following the loss of both parents and lack of siblings.&lt;SEP&gt;The overall state of health or wellbeing of the individual being examined.&lt;SEP&gt;The patient's general condition is being assessed as part of a physical examination.&lt;SEP&gt;The patient's general condition was assessed as part of the physical examination.&lt;SEP&gt;The patient's overall state was assessed during physical examination including vital signs and blood pressure measurement.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ee48a666f78012c5d3d1bc8a9197ad1f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb455f365ca081f8d11526e9a5c93a1d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67002447eb9b8035fd48fe7a9e9c3918&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63bd02d22e1f6638ae07d254e8c8af7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ef91345c594fb99cc0560cc10c6cfa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fea413f23ebde14242287701a5d9f97d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef9a8037991fc6090eb8711c7169f65c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d23944407915efd4d881ed55bdfd0e1f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9f577a1d74b8660a662c322ff0af402&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-39d9dac6bdd47f0ba92b04b21779cdf0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58bd966ed38f72a7a1a3b148a9ff6c74&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c5493bd7b9a1dd3b8744ae06dd09c5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-866f8a930b6453dc13987b3ef91516a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2b258a882645dd7e5231b1bd84b822f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c152973d0da266ffb96eaaa21a1dd9bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e760f3a1d7bb6ec5b4867f0a310494b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af866763d85cb712d130a5292d7aaf32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eedce6d674622ebaf2bc58e14e108a41&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-758501a57caf1471a0236abc020af5db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a9cf6c8e4f4e1598931b827864beac5</data>
