<node id="CHEST">
  <data key="d0">ORGAN</data>
  <data key="d1">The chest was examined thoroughly, revealing a clear and healthy thoracic structure. Auscultation confirmed the presence of clear lung fields bilaterally, indicating no obstruction or fluid buildup in the lungs. The heart sounds were also normal, suggesting that cardiac function is within expected range with regular rhythms and absence of murmurs. Vital organs housed within the chest include the heart and lungs, which are crucial for circulation and respiration respectively. Overall, the data provided indicates a healthy respiratory system and cardiovascular health.</data>
