<node id="ABDOMEN">
  <data key="d0">ORGAN</data>
  <data key="d1">The abdomen is a region of the body that contains vital internal organs such as the liver, spleen, kidneys, stomach, and intestines. It was described in multiple sources as being soft, non-tender, and free of any organomegaly (enlarged liver or spleen), indicating normal abdominal contents without immediate concerns for underlying pathology. In some cases, there was noted tenderness in the lower quadrants without guarding or rebound tenderness, but active bowel sounds were present. The overall examination described a healthy state with no significant abnormalities or distension in the abdominal organs, suggesting that the gastrointestinal system is functioning normally and there are no signs of internal injuries or diseases related to these vital organs.</data>
