ive system responsible for waste elimination.&lt;SEP&gt;The rectum and anus are parts of the digestive system responsible for waste elimination. Here, they were described as normal.&lt;SEP&gt;The rectum and anus are the terminal parts of the digestive tract responsible for waste elimination.&lt;SEP&gt;The rectum and anus were not examined in the assessment.&lt;SEP&gt;The rectum is the final portion of the large intestine where stool is stored before being expelled from the body through the anus.&lt;SEP&gt;These are parts of the large intestine responsible for waste elimination and maintaining bowel health.&lt;SEP&gt;This area was not examined.&lt;SEP&gt;This section was not examined.</data>
