<node id="LYMPH NODES">
  <data key="d0">ORGAN</data>
  <data key="d1">A palpation of the lymph nodes revealed no abnormalities or swelling.&lt;SEP&gt;Assessing lymph nodes for any enlargement which could indicate infection or other conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Examined for size, tenderness, and signs of lymphadenopathy.&lt;SEP&gt;Lymph nodes are evaluated for any enlargement or abnormalities.&lt;SEP&gt;Lymph nodes are small organs that play a key role in the body's immune system by filtering out foreign particles and pathogens.&lt;SEP&gt;Lymph nodes are small, bean-shaped structures involved in filtering lymph fluid and processing immune cells to help fight infection.&lt;SEP&gt;Lymph nodes are small, bean-shaped structures that form part of the lymphatic system. They filter lymph fluid for bacteria and other foreign particles before returning it back into the bloodstream.&lt;SEP&gt;Lymph nodes are small, bean-shaped structures that play a crucial role in the immune system by filtering out foreign particles and producing lymphocytes.&lt;SEP&gt;Lymph nodes help filter lymph fluid, removing bacteria, viruses, and other foreign particles. They may become enlarged due to infection or disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Lymph nodes were noted to be non-palpable during the examination.&lt;SEP&gt;No enlargement of lymph nodes was detected.&lt;SEP&gt;No enlargement or swelling of lymph nodes was detected during palpation.&lt;SEP&gt;No lymphadenopathy noted.&lt;SEP&gt;No lymphadenopathy was observed.&lt;SEP&gt;No palpable lymph nodes detected during examination.&lt;SEP&gt;No palpable lymphadenopathy indicates no significant swelling or infection in the lymph nodes.&lt;SEP&gt;No significant enlargement of the lymph nodes is observed.&lt;SEP&gt;No significant lymphadenopathy was noted.&lt;SEP&gt;Non-palpable lymph nodes imply no active infection in the neck region.&lt;SEP&gt;Not palpable indicates that there are no visible or palpable lymph nodes abnormalities in the patient's neck region.&lt;SEP&gt;Not palpable status of the lymph nodes.&lt;SEP&gt;Palpation of lymph nodes for any enlargement that might suggest an underlying infection or other pathological conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Small glands located throughout the lymphatic system that help filter lymph fluid and produce immune cells.&lt;SEP&gt;The lymph nodes are described as not enlarged, suggesting no abnormal accumulation of immune cells or infection.&lt;SEP&gt;There was no enlargement of lymph nodes.&lt;SEP&gt;There were no significant enlargements observed in the lymph nodes.</data>
