<node id="HEPATITIS A">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">A viral infection affecting the liver, confirmed by elevated liver enzymes (AST 150 U/L, ALT 200 U/L) and bilirubin levels (2.5 mg/dL). The diagnosis is supported by patient history of symptoms and physical examination findings such as hepatomegaly.&lt;SEP&gt;A viral liver infection caused by the Hepatitis A virus, which can lead to severe complications if not treated properly.&lt;SEP&gt;Hepatitis A is a viral liver infection caused by the hepatitis A virus.&lt;SEP&gt;Hepatitis A is an infectious disease caused by the Hepatitis A virus. Symptoms include fatigue, loss of appetite, enlarged liver, and abnormal liver function.&lt;SEP&gt;Hepatitis A is an infectious disease caused by the hepatitis A virus that primarily affects the liver and can cause symptoms such as fatigue, loss of appetite, nausea, abdominal pain, dark urine, clay-colored stools, jaundice, joint pains, and fever.</data>
