<node id="ACUTE ANGLE-CLOSURE GLAUCOMA">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">A condition characterized by a rapid increase in eye pressure leading to potential vision loss if not treated promptly.&lt;SEP&gt;Acute angle-closure glaucoma is a serious eye condition characterized by elevated intraocular pressure, optic nerve damage, and potential vision loss due to increased pressure within the eye caused by insufficient aqueous humor outflow.&lt;SEP&gt;Acute angle-closure glaucoma is a serious eye condition characterized by increased pressure within the eye due to blockage of the drainage system, potentially leading to vision loss if not treated promptly.</data>
