<node id="RIGIDITY OF LIMBS">
  <data key="d0">SYMPTOM</data>
  <data key="d1">A stiff, inflexible feeling of resistance when moving joints through their range of motion.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0e0c934912a4a2b8e642e91965074e81</data>
</node>
<node id="SLOW MOVEMENT">
  <data key="d0">SYMPTOM</data>
  <data key="d1">The disease can cause problems with voluntary movement, making it hard to initiate movements and causing a noticeable slowing down in general motor activity.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0e0c934912a4a2b8e642e91965074e81</data>
</node>
<node id="IN INSTABILITY IN POSTURE">
  <data key="d0">SYMPTOM</data>
  <data key="d1">Difficulty maintaining balance or issues with staying upright for extended periods.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0e0c934912a4a2b8e642e91965074e81</data>
</node>
<node id="CONSTIPATION">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">Difficulty in bowel movements resulting from rectal pressure symptoms.&lt;SEP&gt;Difficulty passing stools, often associated with Parkinson's disease.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-38985301c4d2638f1e8b7e42e74748fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e0c934912a4a2b8e642e91965074e81</data>
</node>
<node id="OLFACTORY DISORDERS">
  <data key="d0">SYMPTOM</data>
  <data key="d1">Loss of sense of smell is a common early symptom of Parkinson’s Disease.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0e0c934912a4a2b8e642e91965074e81</data>
</node>
<node id="SLEEP DISORDERS">
  <data key="d0">SYMPTOM</data>
  <data key="d1">Sleep problems such as insomnia, sleep talking, or waking up frequently during the night are often associated with Parkinson's disease.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0e0c934912a4a2b8e642e91965074e81</data>
</node>
<node id="AUTONOMIC DYSFUNCTION">
  <data key="d0">SYMPTOM</data>
  <data key="d1">This refers to issues with automatic bodily functions like blood pressure regulation and digestion.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0e0c934912a4a2b8e642e91965074e81</data>
</node>
<node id="MENTAL AND COGNITIVE IMPAIRMENTS">
  <data key="d0">SYMPTOM</data>
  <data key="d1">Cognitive decline may include difficulties with memory, attention, decision-making, and problem-solving.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0e0c934912a4a2b8e642e91965074e81</data>
</node>
<node id="NEURODEGENERATIVE DISEASES">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">Conditions characterized by the death or dysfunction of nerve cells over time, leading to various symptoms depending on affected brain regions.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9e05f15b11120fa064748748a32827ec</data>
</node>
