<node id="HEMATOLOGY">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A branch of medicine concerned with blood disorders, requiring specific tests and assays.&lt;SEP&gt;Hematology refers to the study of blood, bone marrow, lymph nodes, and related components such as red blood cells, white blood cells, platelets, and hemoglobin. These elements are crucial for functions like oxygen transport, immune response, and clotting.</data>
