</node>
<node id="REPRODUCTIVE SYSTEM">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">The reproductive system is responsible for producing offspring and includes structures such as ovaries (in females) and testes (in males). It also involves hormones that regulate fertility, menstrual cycles, and other physiological processes related to reproduction.</data>
